      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <section id="measuring-visibility" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Measuring LLM Visibility</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>LLM visibility is measurable through systematic prompt testing across platforms — a monitoring discipline sometimes called AI SERP tracking or generative search monitoring.</strong>
          Unlike traditional rank tracking, which produces a single position number, LLM visibility measurement produces qualitative and quantitative data about how your brand is represented, in which contexts, and alongside which competitors.
        </p>

        <p>
          A basic LLM visibility measurement programme requires: a defined set of target queries (typically 20–50 queries representing the brand's core informational and commercial intent space); a regular testing cadence (weekly or fortnightly); a consistent testing protocol across the target platforms (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, Claude, Copilot); and a scoring framework that records brand mention frequency, mention accuracy, citation presence, and sentiment.
        </p>

        <p>
          The most important metric for LLM visibility work is <em>citation rate</em>: the percentage of target queries for which the brand is mentioned in the AI response. Baseline this on day one of a visibility programme, then track it monthly. Improvements in citation rate that follow specific content or schema changes provide direct attribution data for the tactics driving results.
        </p>

        <p>
          Visibility measurement is also covered in the broader <a href="/ai-brand-visibility/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">AI brand visibility</a> framework. For cross-platform measurement considerations, see our guide to <a href="/cross-model-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">cross-model optimisation</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

